name: ExtensionMolecularSequence_Relative
title: Cross-version Extension `R5.MolecularSequence.relative` for use in FHIR R4
description: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element `MolecularSequence.relative` for use in FHIR R4.
purpose:
This extension is part of the cross-version definitions generated to enable use of the
element `MolecularSequence.relative` as defined in FHIR R5
in FHIR R4.

The source element is defined as:
`MolecularSequence.relative` 0..* `BackboneElement`

Across FHIR versions, the element set has been mapped as:
*  R5: `MolecularSequence.relative` 0..* `BackboneElement`
*  R4B: `MolecularSequence.referenceSeq` 0..1 `BackboneElement`
*  R4: `MolecularSequence.referenceSeq` 0..1 `BackboneElement`

Following are the generation technical comments:
Element `MolecularSequence.relative` has is mapped to FHIR R4 element `MolecularSequence.referenceSeq`, but has no comparisons.
Element `MolecularSequence.relative` has is mapped to FHIR R4 element `MolecularSequence.variant`, but has no comparisons.
